{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01LSr9uT5q65va3v7oe3vujG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ToYpjSzhY1W4nbTrURLZ5i","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":899,"cache_read_input_tokens":13903,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":899,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0118rtZ5YGK1bqAPH91X3aLP","session_id":"baab609c-7354-4992-8237-78467d40b185","uuid":"ca925cb1-57b1-435c-8acb-c6c7bf803a50"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ToYpjSzhY1W4nbTrURLZ5i","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Project Pages Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The projects landing page shows only health dots and a \"View Runs\" link. There is no\n     9→dedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\n    10→or buried in other views.\n    11→\n    12→## Goal\n    13→\n    14→Add a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with four panels:\n    15→\n    16→1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\n    17→2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\n    18→3. **Tasks** — live task pipeline view showing discovered tasks, their status, and assigned runs\n    19→4. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\n    20→\n    21→## Route\n    22→\n    23→```\n    24→GET /projects/{name}\n    25→```\n    26→\n    27→`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\n    28→The handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\n    29→\n    30→Project cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}` instead of\n    31→`/runs?project=X`. The project page includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots)\n    32→and a \"View all runs\" link to the filtered runs list.\n    33→\n    34→## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\n    35→\n    36→### Display\n    37→- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\n    38→- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\n    39→- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\n    40→\n    41→### API additions\n    42→\n    43→```\n    44→GET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\n    45→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\n    46→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\n    47→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\"concurrency\": N}\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→`GET` response:\n    51→```json\n    52→{\n    53→  \"enabled\": true,\n    54→  \"in_flight\": 1,\n    55→  \"concurrency\": 2\n    56→}\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→The orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\n    60→`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\n    61→this flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\n    62→\n    63→Concurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\n    64→\n    65→The Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\n    66→interface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\n    67→`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\n    68→\n    69→## Panel 2: Project Info\n    70→\n    71→### Display\n    72→- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\n    73→  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\n    74→- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\n    75→  design). Display as `v3`.\n    76→- **Prompt files**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show:\n    77→  - Current file contents in a collapsible accordion\n    78→  - Git commit history (short SHA, date, message)\n    79→  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\n    80→\n    81→### API additions\n    82→\n    83→```\n    84→GET /api/projects/{name}/info\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→Response:\n    88→```json\n    89→{\n    90→  \"docker_image\": \"ubuntu:24.04\",\n    91→  \"version\": 3,\n    92→  \"prompt_files\": [\n    93→    {\n    94→      \"path\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\",\n    95→      \"content\": \"Full text of the prompt file...\",\n    96→      \"history\": [\n    97→        {\"sha\": \"abc1234\", \"date\": \"2026-03-05\", \"message\": \"evolution: tighten scope\"},\n    98→        {\"sha\": \"def5678\", \"date\": \"2026-03-01\", \"message\": \"init\"}\n    99→      ]\n   100→    }\n   101→  ]\n   102→}\n   103→```\n   104→\n   105→Implementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\n   106→via `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\n   107→\n   108→```\n   109→GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\n   110→```\n   111→\n   112→Returns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\n   113→\n   114→## Panel 3: Tasks\n   115→\n   116→### Display\n   117→- Table showing discovered tasks: Task ID, Title, Status, Assigned (yes/no), Run link\n   118→- Status badges: `open` (running style), `closed` (succeeded style), other (pending style)\n   119→- Auto-refreshes every 5 seconds via polling\n   120→- Shows \"No tasks discovered\" when the project has no list-tasks output\n   121→\n   122→### API\n   123→\n   124→```\n   125→GET /api/projects/{name}/tasks\n   126→```\n   127→\n   128→Returns the task pipeline state for the project's orchestration loop.\n   129→\n   130→### Runs page changes\n   131→\n   132→- `list-tasks` workflow runs are hidden from the Runs page (both server-rendered and\n   133→  JS-rendered views)\n   134→- Runs with the same `task_id` are grouped under a task header row\n   135→- The `task_id` field is included in the `/api/runs` JSON response\n   136→- Runs without a `task_id` appear ungrouped below task groups\n   137→\n   138→## Panel 4: Workflow View\n   139→\n   140→### Display\n   141→- Two-level tab navigation:\n   142→  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n   143→  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n   144→- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n   145→  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n   146→  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n   147→  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n   148→- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n   149→  - Step name and type\n   150→  - Results list\n   151→  - `max_attempts` if set\n   152→  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\n   153→  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\n   154→  - For host script steps: the `run` command string or contents of the referenced file\n   155→  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n   156→  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n   157→\n   158→### DAG rendering\n   159→Client-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\n   160→layers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\n   161→heuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\n   162→left-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n   163→\n   164→When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\n   165→collector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\n   166→which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. This reduces wire clutter as graphs\n   167→grow in complexity.\n   168→\n   169→The DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n   170→\n   171→### API additions\n   172→\n   173→```\n   174→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n   175→```\n   176→\n   177→Response:\n   178→```json\n   179→[\n   180→  {\n   181→    \"name\": \"develop\",\n   182→    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n   183→    \"location\": \"container\",\n   184→    \"steps\": [\n   185→      {\n   186→        \"name\": \"implement\",\n   187→        \"type\": \"agent\",\n   188→        \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],\n   189→        \"config\": {\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\", \"max_attempts\": null}\n   190→      },\n   191→      ...\n   192→    ],\n   193→    \"wires\": [\n   194→      {\"from\": \"implement\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"test\"},\n   195→      ...\n   196→    ],\n   197→    \"entry_step\": \"implement\"\n   198→  }\n   199→]\n   200→```\n   201→\n   202→The `location` field is either `\"container\"` or `\"host\"`. Host workflows are parsed from\n   203→`.cloche/host.cloche` and included in the same response.\n   204→\n   205→```\n   206→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n   207→```\n   208→\n   209→Returns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\n   210→If the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\n   211→\n   212→## Template / file changes\n   213→\n   214→- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\n   215→- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\"project_detail\"`\n   216→- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\n   217→- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\n   218→\n   219→## Not in scope\n   220→\n   221→- Editing workflow files from the UI\n   222→- Evolution history of workflow structure (just current state)\n   223→- Persisting concurrency overrides to disk\n   224→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0118rtZ5YGK1bqAPH91X3aLP","session_id":"baab609c-7354-4992-8237-78467d40b185","uuid":"7d132ef6-6f56-4bf9-8dc9-419abe9e533f"}
