{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0118rtZ5YGK1bqAPH91X3aLP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive report of the documentation findings.\n\n## Documentation Found That Mentions Step Content Serving\n\nBased on my search of the `docs/` directory, here's what I found:\n\n### Primary Documentation: Project Pages Design\n\n**File:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`\n\nThis document contains the most relevant mentions of step content serving and the web dashboard:\n\n1. **Drawer Panel Section (lines 148-156):**\n   - Describes the right-side drawer panel that opens when clicking a step in the workflow DAG\n   - Specifies what content is displayed for different step types:\n     - **Agent steps**: \"full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\"\n     - **Script steps**: \"the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\"\n     - **Host script steps**: \"the `run` command string or contents of the referenced file\"\n     - **Workflow steps**: displays the dispatched workflow name\n\n2. **Content API Endpoint (lines 205-210):**\n   ```\n   GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n   ```\n   - Documented to \"Returns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text)\"\n   - Notes: \"If the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly\"\n\n### Other Documentation\n\n- **`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`** (lines 152-154): Mentions the `file()` function for referencing script content\n- **`/workspace/docs/SAFETY.md`**: References `.cloche/prompts/` and `.cloche/overrides/` directories but not specific to content serving\n\n### Key Finding\n\nThe documentation **does not mention any restrictions on file types** or specify that content should only come from `.cloche/scripts/`. The current design appears to support serving arbitrary referenced files (prompt files, script files, etc.) based on the workflow configuration. The API endpoint and drawer content mention are agnostic to file location restrictions.\n\n### Documentation Update Needed\n\nIf you're implementing a change to **restrict step content serving to only `.cloche/scripts/` text files** (excluding arbitrary files), you should update:\n\n1. **`docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** — Lines 153-154 specifically, which currently say scripts can come from \"referenced script file\" (implying arbitrary paths), not just `.cloche/scripts/`\n2. **The drawer panel and API endpoint descriptions** (lines 148-210) to clarify that only text files from specific locations are supported\n3. Consider **`docs/USAGE.md`** if it mentions using `file()` for arbitrary file paths"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a30173c4d5d143168 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 35763\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 17248</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"baab609c-7354-4992-8237-78467d40b185","uuid":"56a2f02f-ad02-4232-852c-204b9531b0c8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search docs/ directory for any documentation that mentions step content serving, the web UI drawer, workflow step content API, or binary file handling. Also check for any docs about the web dashboard API endpoints. I need to know if any docs need updating for a change where step content is now only served from .cloche/scripts/ text files (not arbitrary files). Quick search is fine.","agentId":"a30173c4d5d143168","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive report of the documentation findings.\n\n## Documentation Found That Mentions Step Content Serving\n\nBased on my search of the `docs/` directory, here's what I found:\n\n### Primary Documentation: Project Pages Design\n\n**File:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`\n\nThis document contains the most relevant mentions of step content serving and the web dashboard:\n\n1. **Drawer Panel Section (lines 148-156):**\n   - Describes the right-side drawer panel that opens when clicking a step in the workflow DAG\n   - Specifies what content is displayed for different step types:\n     - **Agent steps**: \"full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\"\n     - **Script steps**: \"the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\"\n     - **Host script steps**: \"the `run` command string or contents of the referenced file\"\n     - **Workflow steps**: displays the dispatched workflow name\n\n2. **Content API Endpoint (lines 205-210):**\n   ```\n   GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n   ```\n   - Documented to \"Returns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text)\"\n   - Notes: \"If the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly\"\n\n### Other Documentation\n\n- **`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`** (lines 152-154): Mentions the `file()` function for referencing script content\n- **`/workspace/docs/SAFETY.md`**: References `.cloche/prompts/` and `.cloche/overrides/` directories but not specific to content serving\n\n### Key Finding\n\nThe documentation **does not mention any restrictions on file types** or specify that content should only come from `.cloche/scripts/`. The current design appears to support serving arbitrary referenced files (prompt files, script files, etc.) based on the workflow configuration. The API endpoint and drawer content mention are agnostic to file location restrictions.\n\n### Documentation Update Needed\n\nIf you're implementing a change to **restrict step content serving to only `.cloche/scripts/` text files** (excluding arbitrary files), you should update:\n\n1. **`docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** — Lines 153-154 specifically, which currently say scripts can come from \"referenced script file\" (implying arbitrary paths), not just `.cloche/scripts/`\n2. **The drawer panel and API endpoint descriptions** (lines 148-210) to clarify that only text files from specific locations are supported\n3. Consider **`docs/USAGE.md`** if it mentions using `file()` for arbitrary file paths"}],"totalDurationMs":17248,"totalTokens":35763,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1005,"cache_read_input_tokens":34116,"output_tokens":638,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1005},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
